Common English name: Marbled flathead (
Figs. 13–14
;
Table 5
)

Distribution. Known only from eastern Australia , from off Caloundra Bank, Qld (
26 ° 48 ’S
) to Flinders Island, Tas (
40 °01’S
), including NSW and Vic, on sand near low rocky reefs or on rubble in coastal bays to deep offshore reefs in depths from 20 to 80 m (e.g.,
Paxton & Hanley, 1989
;
Kuiter, 1993
; Hoese et al ., 2008 ; this study).

Size. Maximum length 56 cm (
Grant, 2004
). The largest specimen examined during the present study was 472 mm SL ( 550 mm TL).
